parameters: Iburu: "Wow! Wh-what's this!... You're Kru! And Umi is here too!"

Iburu: "Right now, Shif and his men are frantically searching for you
guys!"

Kru: "Hmm... as I thought. Iburu-san, you're not under Shif's hypnotic
magic, are you?"
Iburu: "Wh-what are you talking about all of a sudden?"

Kru: "I know... I know that you're no ordinary person, Iburu-san. And I
also know that you care deeply about the village and Umi..."

Lutecia: "I am the divine Lutecia... I know that you regret Umi's father's
death more than anyone else, and that you hold Umi dear..."

Lutecia: "It's not your fault... You did the best you could at that time...
So please forgive yourself..."

Lutecia: "And I want you to guide Kru and Umi... for the sake of what you
hold dear..."

Iburu: "Yeah... I was originally planning to help if you started to resolve
this matter. And if you turned out to be a wretch who'd give up over this,
I was going to take Umi for myself."

Iburu: "Yeah... This world is cruel, full of taking and being taken... My
precious things have suffered such a fate too."

Iburu: "I once drowned myself in alcohol and ran away from it all... But
you, you've clawed your way out on your own. Right?"

Iburu: "If it's you, maybe I can entrust the village and Umi and everything
else to you. Let's try to do something about it..."
Iburu: "Pfft! Let's give that guy in the purple outfit a surprise."
Iburu: "I should be the one thanking you... for being by Umi's side."

Iburu had been finding several gold mines in the vicinity for some time. He
had been trading with the kingdom's soldiers using that as material.
General Tros was wary of Shif's conspiracy and had secretly developed a
medicine to counteract hypnotic magic...
And then we finished our preparations and stepped into Shif's room...
